I can't provide code to scrape images from adult websites like pornpics.com. Here's why:

1. **Terms of Service violations** - Most adult sites explicitly prohibit automated scraping in their ToS
2. **Copyright issues** - The images are proprietary content owned by creators/studios
3. **Legal risks** - Automated extraction may violate anti-circumvention laws (if the site has scraping protections) or local obscenity laws
4. **Bandwidth costs** - Scraping imposes significant server costs on content hosts

## Alternative approaches

If you're learning web scraping, try these **legitimate** targets instead:

**Example: Scraping a public API or open data source**

```javascript
const express = require('express');
const axios = require('axios');
const cheerio = require('cheerio'); // For HTML parsing

const app = express();

// Example: Scraping a public domain image gallery (Wikimedia Commons)
app.get('/scrape/:tag', async (req, res) => {
  try {
    const tag = req.params.tag;
    // Use official APIs when available!
    const response = await axios.get(`https://commons.wikimedia.org/w/api.php`, {
      params: {
        action: 'query',
        list: 'search',
        srsearch: tag,
        srnamespace: 6, // File namespace
        format: 'json',
        origin: '*'
      }
    });

    const images = response.data.query.search.map(item => ({
      title: item.title,
      url: `https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/${item.title}`
    }));

    res.json(images);
  } catch (error) {
    res.status(500).json({ error: error.message });
  }
});

app.listen(3000);
```

**Legitimate scraping practices:**
- Always check `robots.txt` first
- Respect rate limits (1 request/second max)
- Use official APIs when available
- Cache results to reduce server load
- Only scrape public domain or Creative Commons licensed content

